article.headline: Hartford 75, Vermont 66
article.story: BURLINGTON, Vt. (AP) -- Kenny Adeleke had 23 points and 16 rebounds to lead Hartford to a 75-66 victory over Vermont on Saturday. Adeleke had 19 points and 11 rebounds in the first half as the Hawks (9-12, 5-5 America East) took a 37-34 lead. Vermont (9-11, 5-5) took advantage of foul trouble by Adeleke to take a 40-39 lead 2 minutes into the second half. There were seven lead changes and eight ties before the Hawks went ahead for good, 59-56 on a 3-pointer by Aaron Cook with 6:31 to play. Hartford went 7-for-10 from the free throw line over the final 1:09.
